1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,377
- [suspenseful music playing]
- [Azuelo] He's the one who killed

2
00:00:02,460 --> 00:00:04,587
Condecido and Vinluan!

3
00:00:04,671 --> 00:00:06,047
Sir, doesn't it bother you?

4
00:00:06,131 --> 00:00:09,259
[Marcus] <i>That CCTV footage</i>
<i>was wiped from our entire system.</i>

5
00:00:09,342 --> 00:00:11,636
Then suddenly, it gets
released anonymously,

6
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:13,763
using an untraceable IP address.

7
00:00:13,847 --> 00:00:16,641
If you want me to believe you, Reyes,

8
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:20,395
bring Datu Rahman to me,
so we can finally know the truth.

9
00:00:20,478 --> 00:00:22,272
You came from Azuelo? What happened?

10
00:00:22,355 --> 00:00:23,189
What did you talk about?

11
00:00:23,273 --> 00:00:24,524
[in English] It's nothing important.

12
00:00:24,607 --> 00:00:26,025
Do you have a problem with me?

13
00:00:26,109 --> 00:00:28,987
[Marcus] <i>I'm sorry, I just have</i>
<i>a lot on my mind right now.</i>

14
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:30,363
[in English] <i>It's nothing personal.</i>

15
00:00:30,447 --> 00:00:34,409
Whoever made this video
is feeding you to the public.

16
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:37,037
Did they bring you in
just to be the fall guy?

17
00:00:37,912 --> 00:00:40,081
[Theresa] <i>Are you upset</i>
<i>because of the video of Datu Rahman</i>

18
00:00:40,165 --> 00:00:41,750
<i>spreading around?</i>

19
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:43,251
He's your father, isn't he?

20
00:00:43,334 --> 00:00:45,712
- I won't judge your father.
- [sobbing]

21
00:00:45,795 --> 00:00:49,257
I hope you won't judge my son
as a murderer, either.

22
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:51,760
[Theresa] <i>Because he's not a bad person.</i>

23
00:00:52,552 --> 00:00:56,056
[Ahmad] <i>Ahmad Mustapha.</i>

24
00:00:56,139 --> 00:00:57,640
What do you need from me?

25
00:00:57,724 --> 00:01:03,063
I want to know what's happening
inside and outside

26
00:01:03,146 --> 00:01:05,815
the NLEA and SID.

27
00:01:05,899 --> 00:01:10,361
[Ahmad] <i>I'll place you inside the NLEA</i>
<i>as an honorable, clean,</i>

28
00:01:10,445 --> 00:01:13,281
<i>and skilled officer from Mindanao.</i>

29
00:01:13,364 --> 00:01:15,116
[Azuelo] <i>Get yourselves together.</i>

30
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,326
He's on his way.

31
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:22,040
[Ahmad] <i>Starting now,</i>
<i>you are Police Major Allan Espina.</i>

32
00:01:22,123 --> 00:01:23,541
[music intensifies, concludes]

33
00:01:28,213 --> 00:01:33,134
[mysterious theme music playing]

34
00:01:43,394 --> 00:01:48,691
[ominous music playing]

35
00:02:10,922 --> 00:02:13,591
[ominous music continues]

36
00:02:35,113 --> 00:02:37,907
Brother, just be patient.

37
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:39,701
Datu Rahman will give in eventually.

38
00:02:42,078 --> 00:02:46,166
[both grunting]

39
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:48,835
Hey!

40
00:02:51,087 --> 00:02:52,881
[suspenseful music playing]

41
00:02:54,257 --> 00:02:57,635
[both grunting]

42
00:02:57,719 --> 00:03:01,848
[Jalil grunting]

43
00:03:01,931 --> 00:03:04,934
[music concludes]

44
00:03:06,686 --> 00:03:08,897
If you need anything,
just let me know, okay?

45
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,819
[sinister music playing]

46
00:03:14,903 --> 00:03:16,154
Did you do that on purpose?

47
00:03:21,784 --> 00:03:22,702
Me?

48
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:27,332
You're the one who bumped into me.

49
00:03:27,957 --> 00:03:29,167
You've got some attitude.

50
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:31,878
Who are you?

51
00:03:34,714 --> 00:03:36,299
Major Allan Espina.

52
00:03:46,643 --> 00:03:49,729
[in English] Welcome
to the Special Investigations Division.

53
00:03:50,313 --> 00:03:52,357
[in English] I'm Director Emil Azuelo.

54
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:53,942
[in English] Good morning, sir.

55
00:03:54,984 --> 00:03:57,111
[in English] Police Major Allan Espina.

56
00:03:57,779 --> 00:03:58,780
[Azuelo] I know.

57
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:01,908
I've already been briefed on your arrival.

58
00:04:02,408 --> 00:04:05,036
And I've reviewed your credentials.

59
00:04:05,536 --> 00:04:06,579
[in English] It's impressive.

60
00:04:06,663 --> 00:04:08,915
[music concludes]

61
00:04:08,998 --> 00:04:10,875
[pensive music playing]

62
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:17,715
Looks like you've already met.

63
00:04:19,217 --> 00:04:20,843
This is Major Espina.

64
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:25,890
He's the special liaison officer
assigned to us by Muslim Affairs.

65
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:29,811
He's been assigned in Mindanao
for more than a decade.

66
00:04:29,894 --> 00:04:33,273
He has deep knowledge of the culture

67
00:04:33,356 --> 00:04:35,525
and way of life of the locals.

68
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:38,319
[in English] The Muslims
consider him a brother.

69
00:04:39,445 --> 00:04:40,780
Even though he's Christian.

70
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:49,122
[tense music continues]

71
00:04:49,205 --> 00:04:50,039
‪[thud]

72
00:04:53,418 --> 00:04:55,128
[Azuelo, in English] Oh, by the way…

73
00:04:55,211 --> 00:04:57,964
This is Agent Lara Angeles.

74
00:04:58,047 --> 00:05:00,425
She's the head agent of the TFA.

75
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:09,434
[pensive music playing]

76
00:05:09,517 --> 00:05:11,853
[Azuelo] And this is Agent Marcus Reyes.

77
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:15,064
He's the supervising agent of the TFA.

78
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:18,609
You'll be working with them
while you are here.

79
00:05:19,193 --> 00:05:23,531
[Jalil] Agent Marcus Reyes,
I'm excited to work with you.

80
00:05:23,614 --> 00:05:25,491
[tense music continues]

81
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:37,420
[Azuelo] I forwarded
an email to both of you.

82
00:05:37,503 --> 00:05:38,963
[in English] Please read it ASAP.

83
00:05:43,134 --> 00:05:45,720
Major Espina, I'll give you a tour.

84
00:05:45,803 --> 00:05:47,055
[in English] Yes, sir.

85
00:05:47,138 --> 00:05:48,139
[Azuelo, in English] Let's go.

86
00:05:55,938 --> 00:05:57,398
[pensive music playing]

87
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:07,950
[pensive music playing]

88
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:13,039
[in English] So he has the authority
to attend operations,

89
00:06:13,122 --> 00:06:17,043
to audit reports, to access evidence.

90
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:18,669
[in English] Everything.

91
00:06:19,253 --> 00:06:22,131
Which means, he can control it, too.

92
00:06:22,215 --> 00:06:24,550
[in English] Yeah. Yeah. Full access.

93
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:27,220
[in English] This is wrong.
[Tagalog] Aren't we gonna do something?

94
00:06:27,804 --> 00:06:29,639
[in English] He… He's not even
a part of our team.

95
00:06:29,722 --> 00:06:31,432
[Marcus] The orders
came from the higher-ups.

96
00:06:31,516 --> 00:06:33,017
[Lara gasps]

97
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:34,352
There's nothing we can do.

98
00:06:34,435 --> 00:06:37,021
[Lara breathes heavily]

99
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:38,064
[sighs]

100
00:06:38,147 --> 00:06:39,482
[pensive music continues]

101
00:06:39,565 --> 00:06:45,613
- [exhales]
- [Lara breathes heavily]

102
00:06:45,696 --> 00:06:49,033
[sighs]

103
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:53,287
[pensive music playing]

104
00:06:54,622 --> 00:06:58,042
This is where we detained
Datu Rahman before he escaped.

105
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:05,842
[intriguing music playing]

106
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:11,889
Major Espina,

107
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:14,600
why did you want to see this cell?

108
00:07:16,185 --> 00:07:17,520
I just wanted to study it.

109
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:23,109
Is it okay for you to leave me here?

110
00:07:23,609 --> 00:07:26,154
I'd like to survey it closer.

111
00:07:27,155 --> 00:07:27,989
[exhales]

112
00:07:28,072 --> 00:07:29,365
Alright.

113
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:31,492
I'll be waiting for you in my office.

114
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:33,077
Thank you.

115
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:36,914
[tense music playing]

116
00:07:41,377 --> 00:07:42,920
Find everything.

117
00:07:43,004 --> 00:07:44,964
[in English] I want his files,
credentials, background, everything.

118
00:07:45,756 --> 00:07:46,757
[man, in English] Copy, ma'am.

119
00:07:49,427 --> 00:07:51,262
[rapid beeping]

120
00:07:51,345 --> 00:07:52,180
Ma'am?

121
00:07:52,263 --> 00:07:55,892
[intriguing music playing]

122
00:08:07,069 --> 00:08:12,325
[music intensifies]

123
00:08:12,408 --> 00:08:14,952
- [beeping]
- [Lara] That's it? That's all we have?

124
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:16,579
[in English] I want more!

125
00:08:16,662 --> 00:08:19,874
Find me personal files,
background, education.

126
00:08:19,957 --> 00:08:22,001
Where did he study? What year?
[in English] Everything!

127
00:08:22,084 --> 00:08:23,377
[in English] On it, ma'am.

128
00:08:25,838 --> 00:08:27,924
- [keyboard clacking]
- [whizzing]

129
00:08:29,383 --> 00:08:31,302
[intriguing music playing]

130
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:46,901
[sinister music playing]

131
00:08:58,871 --> 00:08:59,914
Papa…

132
00:09:04,877 --> 00:09:07,672
I'll find you.

133
00:09:08,256 --> 00:09:09,215
[sniffles]

134
00:09:10,049 --> 00:09:13,261
I'll find the monsters

135
00:09:14,178 --> 00:09:18,766
who ruined your life and killed our town.

136
00:09:18,849 --> 00:09:24,272
[intriguing music continues]

137
00:09:30,653 --> 00:09:31,696
[sniffles]

138
00:09:33,281 --> 00:09:36,242
[suspenseful music playing]

139
00:09:40,705 --> 00:09:41,706
Ma'am…

140
00:09:41,789 --> 00:09:43,624
[pensive music playing]

141
00:09:44,834 --> 00:09:46,043
It's restricted.

142
00:09:46,127 --> 00:09:47,336
Classified Level 5.

143
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:49,672
Bypass it and check again.

144
00:09:49,755 --> 00:09:51,507
- [beeping]
- [man] I can't do that, ma'am.

145
00:09:52,341 --> 00:09:54,802
Only higher-ups have access to this.

146
00:09:54,885 --> 00:09:56,262
If we try to bypass it,

147
00:09:56,345 --> 00:09:58,306
we'll trigger the alarm
on the main system.

148
00:09:58,389 --> 00:09:59,473
They'll find out it's us.

149
00:09:59,557 --> 00:10:03,311
I think they expected someone
would check his personal files.

150
00:10:03,394 --> 00:10:10,026
[music intensifies]

151
00:10:16,198 --> 00:10:20,369
[suspenseful music playing]

152
00:10:25,958 --> 00:10:28,461
[Lara] <i>What are you hiding, Major Espina?</i>

153
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:32,882
- <i>And who's protecting you?</i>
- [beeping]

154
00:10:32,965 --> 00:10:33,799
‪[music intensifies]

155
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:44,935
[music intensifies]

156
00:10:47,688 --> 00:10:52,943
[tense music playing]

157
00:11:16,175 --> 00:11:17,093
[Ahmad] Jalil.

158
00:11:18,010 --> 00:11:21,847
This is Task Force Alpha.

159
00:11:23,099 --> 00:11:28,771
They handle all cases
of gun smuggling in the country.

160
00:11:29,271 --> 00:11:32,191
Let me introduce them one by one.

161
00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:34,735
Lara Angeles.

162
00:11:36,445 --> 00:11:40,324
She's the head agent of the Task Force.

163
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:44,870
[Ahmad] <i>Which means,</i>
<i>she's the brain of it all.</i>

164
00:11:44,954 --> 00:11:45,788
[suspenseful music playing]

165
00:11:45,871 --> 00:11:49,375
From raids, to gathering of evidence,

166
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:52,628
to submitting reports from the Task Force.

167
00:11:52,711 --> 00:11:58,926
<i>She's the adoptive daughter</i>
<i>of Retired General Manuel Carillo.</i>

168
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:06,434
SPO2 Sean Suarez.

169
00:12:06,517 --> 00:12:08,561
According to his peers,

170
00:12:09,353 --> 00:12:12,940
this man is quiet, observant,

171
00:12:13,524 --> 00:12:15,818
and a skilled sniper.

172
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:23,159
This one is Felix Domingo.

173
00:12:24,118 --> 00:12:27,955
They say he's good with guns and knives.

174
00:12:28,539 --> 00:12:30,124
[Ahmad] <i>I heard</i>
<i>he's the most violent of all.</i>

175
00:12:31,417 --> 00:12:32,543
<i>He's cunning.</i>

176
00:12:32,626 --> 00:12:36,589
So be careful when talking to him.

177
00:12:36,672 --> 00:12:40,509
He could kill you
with a smile on his face.

178
00:12:42,303 --> 00:12:46,098
These are the original members of NLEA

179
00:12:47,141 --> 00:12:48,851
that are remaining.

180
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:51,187
Now.

181
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:53,689
This is the one they call
the "Golden Boy".

182
00:12:54,398 --> 00:12:56,567
Marcus Reyes.

183
00:12:57,902 --> 00:12:59,987
They say he's the best of the best.

184
00:13:01,113 --> 00:13:03,407
They say that he has
excellent credentials.

185
00:13:04,283 --> 00:13:06,452
An impeccably good investigator.

186
00:13:06,535 --> 00:13:08,871
And, as you know,

187
00:13:09,413 --> 00:13:13,042
he was the one who led
the raid on your island.

188
00:13:14,668 --> 00:13:15,503
[breathes heavily]

189
00:13:15,586 --> 00:13:16,545
Jalil.

190
00:13:17,296 --> 00:13:20,549
That was his very first failure.

191
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:24,428
As well as Task Force Alpha's.

192
00:13:26,347 --> 00:13:30,809
They are your jump-off point.

193
00:13:31,393 --> 00:13:33,020
You'll get to know them,

194
00:13:33,646 --> 00:13:35,606
make friends with them,

195
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:40,528
you'll get all the information
we're gonna need.

196
00:13:41,028 --> 00:13:42,321
I believe

197
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:47,076
that they are the key

198
00:13:47,993 --> 00:13:51,497
for us to know all the secrets
of the Task Force.

199
00:13:51,997 --> 00:13:54,625
[music intensifies]

200
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:01,173
[Felix, indistinct]

201
00:14:01,257 --> 00:14:02,591
[Felix laughing]

202
00:14:02,675 --> 00:14:04,218
[Felix] Looks like you had
a lot to drink last night.

203
00:14:04,301 --> 00:14:06,345
- [Suarez] Kinda, kinda.
- [Felix] You're still hungover.

204
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:07,846
- [Felix laughing]
- [indistinct speech]

205
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:10,516
- [Suarez] Sure.
- [Felix] Let's go again later!

206
00:14:10,599 --> 00:14:12,810
- [Felix] Can you handle it?
- [Suarez] How about him, sir?

207
00:14:12,893 --> 00:14:14,562
- [Felix] But he left already.
- [Felix and Suarez laugh]

208
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:16,105
SPO4 Domingo.

209
00:14:16,188 --> 00:14:17,273
[tense music playing]

210
00:14:17,356 --> 00:14:19,275
SPO2 Suarez.

211
00:14:20,734 --> 00:14:23,863
I am Police Major Allan Espina.

212
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:25,948
Sir.

213
00:14:27,575 --> 00:14:28,784
[clears throat]

214
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:30,160
Major Espina.

215
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,164
[Felix] Ah!

216
00:14:34,248 --> 00:14:39,003
So you're the Special Liaison Officer
from the… [clicks tongue]

217
00:14:39,086 --> 00:14:40,462
Muslim Affairs!

218
00:14:40,546 --> 00:14:41,922
[chuckling]

219
00:14:42,006 --> 00:14:45,467
Sir, word gets around here pretty fast.

220
00:14:46,176 --> 00:14:48,470
But, sir, what's gonna happen now?

221
00:14:48,554 --> 00:14:51,765
Does that mean you'll
always stick around us?

222
00:14:52,349 --> 00:14:53,309
That's right.

223
00:14:53,809 --> 00:14:55,185
Seems to be the case.

224
00:14:56,478 --> 00:14:59,106
Then, we should get along.

225
00:14:59,189 --> 00:15:00,190
Am I right?

226
00:15:00,691 --> 00:15:02,109
You know Sean over here?

227
00:15:02,192 --> 00:15:03,527
We didn't get along before,

228
00:15:03,611 --> 00:15:05,446
but when I started bringing him along
to you know what…

229
00:15:05,529 --> 00:15:06,780
[Felix laughs]

230
00:15:06,864 --> 00:15:09,617
To our trips to the bar…

231
00:15:10,784 --> 00:15:12,578
[unsettling music playing]

232
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:20,878
[music becomes suspenseful]

233
00:15:25,549 --> 00:15:26,800
[phone ringing]

234
00:15:26,884 --> 00:15:29,428
Brother. I'm heading over.

235
00:15:29,511 --> 00:15:31,597
- I need to talk to Datu Rahman.
- [engine starts]

236
00:15:36,185 --> 00:15:40,814
[suspenseful music playing]

237
00:15:55,371 --> 00:15:58,290
[music intensifies]

238
00:16:31,281 --> 00:16:34,159
[music intensifies]

239
00:16:45,379 --> 00:16:48,882
[music fades out]

240
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:52,469
[ominous music playing]

241
00:17:23,751 --> 00:17:28,380
[ominous music continues]

242
00:17:58,577 --> 00:18:02,539
[music intensifies]

243
00:18:05,417 --> 00:18:06,835
[Marcus] Why are you tailing me?

244
00:18:06,919 --> 00:18:09,546
[suspenseful sting]

245
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:15,260
- [both grunting]
- [tense, dramatic music playing]

246
00:18:15,344 --> 00:18:17,054
Make one mistake.

247
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:18,305
I won't hesitate to shoot.

248
00:18:20,599 --> 00:18:21,975
I'd like to see you try.

249
00:18:22,893 --> 00:18:24,228
I won't hesitate, either.

250
00:18:24,311 --> 00:18:25,729
[suspenseful sting]

251
00:18:41,703 --> 00:18:46,792
[both grunting, groaning]

252
00:18:46,875 --> 00:18:49,253
[grunts]

253
00:18:49,336 --> 00:18:50,838
[tense, dramatic music playing]

254
00:18:52,214 --> 00:18:54,466
I know you've been tailing me
since earlier.

255
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:56,218
[music intensifies]

256
00:18:56,301 --> 00:18:58,095
What do you need from me?

257
00:18:58,178 --> 00:19:00,430
I'm doing my job.

258
00:19:00,514 --> 00:19:01,807
I’m keeping an eye on you.

259
00:19:01,890 --> 00:19:04,393
We are outside office premises,

260
00:19:04,476 --> 00:19:05,477
yet you’re still tailing me.

261
00:19:05,561 --> 00:19:08,105
Why? Did the Zamboanga massacre happen

262
00:19:08,188 --> 00:19:10,107
inside office premises?

263
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:14,403
All illegal acts happen outside.

264
00:19:14,486 --> 00:19:16,321
[music intensifies]

265
00:19:22,786 --> 00:19:25,164
[music subdues]

266
00:19:34,631 --> 00:19:35,841
Don’t follow me again.

267
00:19:37,634 --> 00:19:39,219
I don’t want you on my tail.

268
00:19:41,889 --> 00:19:44,933
Those people didn’t want
to die either, did they?

269
00:19:46,059 --> 00:19:48,187
But that's exactly what happened.

270
00:19:48,937 --> 00:19:53,025
[music intensifies]

271
00:20:01,366 --> 00:20:02,618
‪[music intensifies, concludes]

272
00:20:03,535 --> 00:20:07,289
[suspenseful music playing]

273
00:20:07,372 --> 00:20:10,375
[Jalil] Those people didn’t want
<i>to die either, did they?</i>

274
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:13,754
<i>But that's exactly what happened.</i>

275
00:20:14,796 --> 00:20:17,549
- [gunshots]
- [people screaming]

276
00:20:22,721 --> 00:20:25,057
- [people screaming]
- [gunshots]

277
00:20:38,153 --> 00:20:40,364
Why are you doing this?

278
00:20:41,448 --> 00:20:44,076
[engine revving]

279
00:20:44,159 --> 00:20:45,827
[shouts]

280
00:20:45,911 --> 00:20:46,954
[frustrated shout]

281
00:20:47,037 --> 00:20:48,330
[breathes heavily]

282
00:20:52,793 --> 00:20:57,339
[pensive music playing]

283
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:14,273
[exhales heavily]

284
00:21:26,910 --> 00:21:31,665
[music intensifies]

285
00:21:45,304 --> 00:21:49,099
THE VIRAL VIDEO OF DATU RAHMAN
KILLING TWO POLICE OFFICERS

286
00:21:50,475 --> 00:21:53,437
[Jalil] <i>Why are they</i>
<i>doing this to you, Father?</i>

287
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:58,317
[pensive music playing]

288
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:02,487
<i>I can’t stomach working with the people</i>
<i>who massacred our community.</i>

289
00:22:03,864 --> 00:22:07,576
<i>But I can't let my emotions</i>
<i>get in the way.</i>

290
00:22:11,872 --> 00:22:13,832
[reciting prayer in Arabic]

291
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:17,294
- [Jalil] <i>I need to fulfill my mission.</i>
- [mutters prayer]

292
00:22:18,712 --> 00:22:20,255
[reciting prayer in Arabic]

293
00:22:22,466 --> 00:22:25,469
[Jalil] <i>I will find out</i>
<i>who’s behind all of this.</i>

294
00:22:26,595 --> 00:22:30,807
<i>For you, Father. And for our village.</i>

295
00:22:34,311 --> 00:22:38,356
[somber music playing]

296
00:22:39,232 --> 00:22:40,067
‪[inaudible]

297
00:22:42,569 --> 00:22:45,781
- [tense music playing]
- [rapid clicking]

298
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:00,045
‪[rapid clicking]

299
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:15,185
‪-[rapid clicking]
‪-[music intensifies]

300
00:23:27,823 --> 00:23:31,785
[music intensifies]

301
00:23:41,002 --> 00:23:42,504
‪[loud thud]

302
00:23:47,551 --> 00:23:50,011
[Lara] <i>Why can't I access your records?</i>

303
00:23:50,095 --> 00:23:53,014
<i>What are you hiding, Espina?</i>

304
00:23:53,598 --> 00:23:54,975
[in English] <i>What are you?</i>

305
00:23:55,058 --> 00:23:57,936
- [intriguing music playing]
- [inaudible]

306
00:23:59,354 --> 00:24:01,356
[Lara] <i>Are you an agent deep undercover?</i>

307
00:24:02,566 --> 00:24:05,443
<i>What do you want?</i>

308
00:24:13,535 --> 00:24:19,082
[music intensifies]

309
00:24:22,210 --> 00:24:23,170
Do not look for me.

310
00:24:23,253 --> 00:24:24,796
[Jalil] <i>This is for your own good.</i>

311
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:28,633
It’s highly unlikely that Datu Rahman
is responsible for the killings.

312
00:24:28,717 --> 00:24:32,262
That is why you must find him,
so we can uncover the truth!

313
00:24:32,345 --> 00:24:36,433
[Jalil] <i>I need to know why</i>
<i>they massacred our community.</i>

314
00:24:36,516 --> 00:24:38,393
You can't access that.

315
00:24:38,476 --> 00:24:40,729
But I already did.

316
00:24:40,812 --> 00:24:42,314
[tense music playing]

317
00:24:42,397 --> 00:24:47,569
Build a new Task Force Alpha
to catch these criminals.

318
00:24:47,652 --> 00:24:51,281
What if they just kill our new members?

319
00:24:51,364 --> 00:24:52,407
How will I tell their families?

320
00:24:52,490 --> 00:24:54,576
[in English] Well, somebody
has to do the job!

321
00:24:54,659 --> 00:24:57,412
Death is part of the job,
and we accept the risk.

322
00:24:57,495 --> 00:25:03,293
I will be involved in selecting
new members of Task Force Alpha.

323
00:25:05,170 --> 00:25:06,171
Who do you think you are?

324
00:25:06,254 --> 00:25:08,340
I know you have jurisdiction over us,

325
00:25:08,423 --> 00:25:10,675
but do not dare disrespect
our fallen comrades!

326
00:25:10,759 --> 00:25:12,802
- Oh, did I?
- Yes! You did!

327
00:25:12,886 --> 00:25:14,554
What about the people
who died on the island?!

328
00:25:14,638 --> 00:25:16,681
[Jalil] <i>Did you consider how they felt?</i>

329
00:25:16,765 --> 00:25:19,809
[music concludes]
